
Within a three-week period in September, Fulton schools' enrollment of Hurricane Katrina students more than doubled, according to the latest figures the school district released. Officials say 1,081 students whose families were displaced by the storm had joined Fulton classrooms by Sept. 30, compared with 519 by Sept. 9. Elementary, middle and high schools in Sandy Springs' North Springs/ Riverwood cluster took in 193 students, the highest number compared with other groups of north Fulton schools. 

